  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The dough needs 30 minutes in the fridge before rolling. A warm dough sticks to the work surface and loses its edges when cut; a chilled dough rolls cleanly to 4 to 5 mm and lifts without distorting. Roll directly on a lightly floured surface and cut firmly so the cutter goes cleanly through. Biscuits baked from properly chilled dough will hold whatever shape you cut."
          }
        ]
      },
